    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 4.94,
      "text": "This is a LibraVox recording. All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.7,
      "end": 10.92,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.66,
      "end": 16.46,
      "text": "Recorded by Lee Dunkleberg, Fort Worth, Texas, Dunkleberg.com.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.74,
      "end": 21.18,
      "text": "ASOP's Fables, the Oxen and the Butchers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 22.78,
      "end": 33.18,
      "text": "Once upon a time, the Oxen determined to be revengeed upon the Butchers for the havoc they wrought in their ranks,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 34.06,
      "end": 38.74,
      "text": "and plotted to put them to death on a given day.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 39.44,
      "end": 44.86,
      "text": "They were all gathered together discussing how best to carry out the plan,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 44.86,
      "end": 50.66,
      "text": "and the more violent of them were engaged in sharpening their horns for the fray.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 51.52,
      "end": 54.44,
      "text": "When an old Ox got up upon his feet and said,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 55.52,
      "end": 62.74,
      "text": "Well, our brothers, you have good reason I know to hate these Butchers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 63.7,
      "end": 73.82,
      "text": "But at any rate, they understand their trade and do what they have to do without causing unnecessary pain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 74.92,
      "end": 82.2,
      "text": "But if we kill them, others who have no experience will be set to slaughter us,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 82.62,
      "end": 88.04,
      "text": "and will by their bungling inflict great sufferings upon us.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 88.86,
      "end": 92.88,
      "text": "For you may be sure that even though all the Butchers perish,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 94.12,
      "end": 97.62,
      "text": "mankind will never go without their beef.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 98.94,
      "end": 101.54,
      "text": "End of the Oxen and the Butchers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 103.82,
      "end": 106.12,
      "text": "End of the Oxen and the Butchers.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
